  "prompt": "What is the AT&T wireless voicemail number?",
  "response": "The AT&T wireless voicemail number typically depends on your specific location and whether you're calling from your AT&T phone or another phone. Here are the general instructions to access your AT&T voicemail:\n\n### From Your AT&T Wireless Phone:\n1. **Press and hold the \"1\" key** on your phone's keypad.\n2. This will automatically call your AT&T voicemail.\n3. Follow the prompts to enter your password and listen to your messages.\n\n### From Another Phone:\n1. Dial **+1 (805) 637-7249** (this is the general AT&T voicemail access number).\n2. When prompted, enter your AT&T wireless phone number.\n3. Follow the instructions to enter your voicemail password and access your messages.\n\nIf you're traveling internationally, you may need to use the international voicemail access number: **+1 (314) 925-6925**.\n\nMake sure your phone is set up with voicemail, and you have a password ready to access your messages. If you\u2019re having trouble, contact AT&T customer support for assistance.",
